          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were produced by evaporation of metallic,",
                "highly enriched (93.1%) 113In, (142 microg/cm2) onto",
                "thin carbon foil(~40 microg/cm2)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "49-IN-113",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.931
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 7 ion-implanted silicon detectors with active",
                "areas of 50 mm2 and 500 microm thickness were used to",
                "measure the angular distributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The detectors were collimated with about 1 mm wide",
                "slits. Two detectors with angular separation of 10",
                "degrees were mounted on the upper turntable, to measure",
                "the yield of the scattered alpha particles at forward",
                "angles. Five detectors were placed on the lower",
                "turntable with angular separation of 5 degree.",
                "The solid angle was typically within (1.0-1.6)10-4 sr.",
                "Two other detectors were mounted on the wall of the",
                "chamber at +-15 degree to monitor the beam intensity.",
                "Complete angular distributions between 20 and 175",
                "degrees were measured at energies of E=16.15 and",
                "E=19.50 MeV in 1 degree and 2.5 degree  steps."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The energy spread of the initial beam energy",
                " was 100 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The count rates have been normalized to the",
                "yield of the monitor detectors at 15 degree.",
                "The relative measurement eliminates the typical",
                "uncertainties of absolute measurements, coming mainly",
                "from changes in the absolute target thickness and from",
                "the beam current integration. Total uncertainty was",
                "between 4% and 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
